Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: "Credentials cache file not found"

Solution: Authenticate first using kinit username@REALM
Verify cache location: echo $KRB5CCNAME or check /tmp/krb5cc_$(id -u)
Issue: "Permission denied" when accessing cache

Solution: Ensure cache file has correct permissions (600)
Run: chmod 600 /tmp/krb5cc_$(id -u)
Issue: "Clock skew too great" error

Solution: Synchronize system time with KDC
Run: sudo ntpdate -s time.nist.gov or configure NTP
Issue: Injected tickets not working

Solution: Verify ticket hasn't expired using klist -v
Ensure realm and principal names match exactly
Check that KDC is accessible
Issue: Service ticket request fails

Solution: Verify service principal exists in KDC
Check DNS resolution for service hostname
Ensure TGT is valid and not expired
