Security Implications: Ticket theft is a serious attack vector. Organizations should:

Implement credential guard and protected processes
Monitor for unusual ticket requests
Use short ticket lifetimes
Enable audit logging for authentication events
Implement network segmentation
Defensive Measures:

Enable AES encryption for Kerberos
Implement Protected Users security group
Use Privileged Access Workstations (PAWs)
Monitor for Pass-the-Ticket attacks
Regularly rotate service account passwords
